Title : Kshaoom Indian Reserve No. 23
Text : '''Kshaoom Indian Reserve No. 23''', officially '''Kshaoom 23''', 2.3 hectares in size, is an [[Indian reserve]] on the northwest tip of [[De Horsey Island]],<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/64718.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Kshaoom 23 (Indian reserve)"]</ref> which is immediately south of the [[Tsimpsean Peninsula]] at the mouth of the [[Skeena River]] in the [[British Columbia Coast|North Coast region]] of [[British Columbia]], Canada.  It and [[Dashken Indian Reserve No. 22]], across [[De Horsey Passage]] on the east tip of [[Smith Island (British Columbia)|Smith Island]], are shared between the [[Metlakatla, British Columbia|Metlakatla]] and [[Lax Kw'alaams]] [[band government]]s.<ref>[http://pse5-esd5.ainc-inac.gc.ca/FNP/Main/Search/RVDetail.aspx?RESERVE_NUMBER=07762&lang=eng Indian and Northern Affairs Canada Reserve/Settlement/Village Detail]</ref>

